  "text": "The Java class loading delegation chain in OpenJDK follows a parent-first delegation model implemented across multiple layers:\n\n## Java Layer\n\n**ClassLoader.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java): The foundation of the delegation chain is the `loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method (line 534), which implements parent-first delegation. The method:\n1. First checks if the class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass(name)` (line 539)\n2. If not found, delegates to the parent class loader with `parent.loadClass(name, false)` (line 544)\n3. Or searches the bootstrap loader with `findBootstrapClassOrNull(name)` (line 546)\n4. If still not found, invokes `findClass(name)` to load locally (line 557)\n\n**BuiltinClassLoader.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java): The base class (line 89) for the three built-in loaders. It extends SecureClassLoader and implements a custom `findClass()` method (line 512) that maps class names to modules and searches for classes within the appropriate loader's search path.\n\n**ClassLoaders.java** (src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java): Creates the three built-in class loaders in a static initialization block (line 63):\n- **BootClassLoader** (line 131): Extends BuiltinClassLoader with no parent, delegates to JLA.findBootstrapClassOrNull()\n- **PlatformClassLoader** (line 146): Extends BuiltinClassLoader with BootClassLoader as parent\n- **AppClassLoader** (line 161): Extends BuiltinClassLoader with PlatformClassLoader as parent\n\n## Native Layer\n\n**classLoader.cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp): Implements native class loading. The main function is `ClassLoader::load_class()` (line 1141) which is called by the boot classloader. It:\n1. Converts class names to file names (line 1151)\n2. Searches multiple locations in order: --patch-module entries (line 1177), jimage/exploded build (line 1183), and boot classpath append entries (line 1195)\n3. Opens and reads class file streams from the appropriate classpath entry\n\n## Class Caching Layer\n\n**systemDictionary.hpp/cpp** (src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp and systemDictionary.cpp): Maintains a cache of loaded classes. The SystemDictionary class (line 78 in .hpp) provides:\n- `resolve_or_fail()` (line 92): Loads and caches a class, throwing an exception if not found\n- `resolve_or_null()` (line 100): Loads and caches a class, returning null if not found\n- `resolve_with_circularity_detection()` (line 106): Handles circular class dependencies\n\nThe delegation chain flows from Java application code → ClassLoader.loadClass() → BuiltinClassLoader.findClass() → JNI call to native ClassLoader::load_class() → SystemDictionary::resolve_or_fail() for caching and resolution."
}

